function c10_king() {
  const motiveLine = {
    revenge: `"You know what it is to be wronged and disbelieved," you say quietly. "You carried MY cause once, when the whole court called it madness. I've carried yours ten days through the fens. Get up, Alden. Debts run both directions."`,
    glory: `"They're already singing the Protector's song in your city," you say. "Songs get one ending each, and his is half-written. I walked ten days to offer you the other one — the one where the King comes BACK. That's the verse they never forget."`,
    knowledge: `"I don't deal in faith anymore," you say, opening the dispatch case. "Only in what's written. Read your own margin-note, sire. Then read the scout-reports it trusted — signed by men who were never born. You weren't a coward. You were a PROOF, in a theorem he built. Help me show the working."`,
    wealth: `"He paid Zarga with your treasury and billed you for the theft," you say. "You're not a coward, sire — you're COLLATERAL. And I have never once in my life let a debt like that stand unbalanced. Get up. We're going to collect."`,
    protector: `"Your city is starving quietly and disappearing loudly," you say, "and the man doing it wears your friendship like a stolen cloak. I stood up for THEM when standing was treason. I need the man who taught the realm what standing looks like. They don't need a martyr in a ruin. They need their King."`,
    wanderlust: `"I've walked every road out of Ironvale," you say, "and I just walked the only one that matters — ten days of fen, to this fire. Every road home is closed to you EXCEPT the one through his lies. It's a hard road. I happen to know it. Walk it with me."`
  }[C.motive.id];
  scene(pArt("alden"), "The Man Who Was King",
    [ `Alden sits apart from the fire, sharpening a warhammer that is already sharp — a big man made smaller by the only wound that ever got past his guard. He hears your report — the exoneration, the framing, the forged letter read to ten thousand booing citizens — without moving. When you finish, he speaks to the whetstone.`,
      `"The barons showed me the letters. My madness, my cowardice, my thieving — in dispatches that arrived before I did. Thaddeus always was <i>thorough</i>." The stone rasps. "I keep thinking: forty years. Every kindness a brick. He built me like a wall builds a gate — trusted, load-bearing, and made to be OPENED." He finally looks up, and his eyes are terrible. "Why have you come, hero? To see what's left?"`,
      `<i>${motiveLine}</i>`,
      `The whetstone stops. For a long moment the only sound is the fire. Then — slowly, like siege engines being winched taut — King Alden stands, and the eleven knights around the fire rise with him without a single order given.`,
      `"The catacomb orders," he says. "The manifest. The insurance." His voice has iron in it again, and — Dawnmother help whoever's schedule this ruins — <i>patience</i>. "Then we do this LAWFULLY. Zarga's proof first. Then the barons, at open moot. Then my city." A pause. "And then Thaddeus."` ],
    [ { txt: "💀 East, to Zarga's war camp — the insurance comes first", onclick: "flags.kingRestored = true; addTruth(5,'a fen-trapper swears she saw the King — ALIVE, and armed'); grantXp(400,'the King rises'); goScene('c10_zarga')" } ]);
